          "error_notes": [
            "2026-06-23: Initially chose revenue (the business GOAL) as the North Star, conflating goal with NSM -- the canonical mistake. Corrected after one prompt; then chose 'completed deliveries' (value proxy that leads revenue), decomposed cleanly into active users x deliveries per user, and correctly placed average delivery time as a deeper driver feeding both branches. Re-test COLD next session: does the goal-vs-NSM separation hold without prompting? That is the interview crux.",
            "2026-06-25: Cold re-test PASSED unaided -- for Spotify picked total time streamed as the NSM and separated it from revenue (the business goal) with no prompt. The goal-vs-NSM crux now holds cold. Next sharpening: frame the NSM as the leading proxy for value that drives the lagging revenue goal, not just 'revenue can be gamed.'"
          ]
        },
