          "error_notes": [
            "2026-06-23: Guardrail concept INTRODUCED (taught: a guardrail catches when winning on the NSM causes damage elsewhere; almost any NSM can be gamed). The NSM-vs-goal distinction was practiced via the metric-trees topic. No unaided guardrail attempt yet -- session ended before he answered. First retrieval owed next session: name a guardrail for an NSM and the specific failure it guards against.",
            "2026-06-25: First retrieval after teaching, and it landed. Initially conflated guardrail with input/decomposition metrics (guessed 'streams per user' / 'number of users'); after a short re-teach, produced two correct guardrails with named failures unaided -- Instagram time-spent guarded by churn/uninstalls (catches annoying users into leaving), YouTube watch-time guarded by average completion % (catches clickbait inflation). Graduated past first-contact (bloom Apply, 2 unaided-correct). Cold re-test next session that he does not revert to input metrics; push toward a wellbeing/satisfaction guardrail that catches harm before churn.",
            "2026-06-30: Cold re-test (Duolingo). Did NOT revert to input metrics and did NOT pick the goal -- both prior traps cleared. New gap surfaced: picked a per-attempt QUALITY RATE (spaced-recall correct rate) as the NSM, plus a quality guardrail (transfer rate) -- both quality, nothing capturing engaged value at scale / leading business growth. After one prompt, correctly converted the rate into a volume-at-scale aggregate (sum of correct spaced recalls across users = quality x scale). Borderline: needed the prompt to get the NSM's scale+leading-indicator role; articulation loose. Calibration note: conf 80 on a shaky answer = overconfident here (+0.3), unusual vs his usual underconfidence. Next: state the NSM crisply as an aggregate count of value events (not a rate), and name why it leads revenue."
          ]
        },
